  "text": "More recently, n-3 PUFAs have been demonstrated to influence the activation or expression of various transcription factors, including peroxisome proliferator activated receptors (PPARs), hepatic nuclear-4α (HNF-4α), nuclear factor κB (NF-κB), retinoid X receptor α (RXRα), sterol regulatory element binding protein-1c (SREBP-1c), and liver X receptors (LXR) [CITATION_1] . Therefore feeding animals with an n-3 PUFAs enriched diet could make dramatic transcriptional changes in animal tissues.",
